==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Faint-hearted
<hw>Faint"-heart`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Wanting in
courage; depressed by fear; easily discouraged or frightened; cowardly;
timorous; dejected.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fear not, neither be <qex>faint-hearted</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Is.
vii. 4.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Faint"-heart`ed*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Faint"-heart`ed*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fainting</ent>⟦br⟧
